    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-6">
        <h2 class="HeaderA-Level2 mb-4">What Is An Information <br>Security Event?</h2>
        <p class="lh-17">A security event is an observable change in the normal operation of a network, IT service, website or application that identifies when a security policy or safeguard has failed. Security events are usually tied to systems, applications or data that play a significant role in the overall security of the system.</p>
        <p class="lh-17">cWatch Web’s Security & Event Management (SIEM) sofware is used to identify these events for you and offer the ability to manage them by providing real-time analysis, alerts and context so humans can quickly investigate before it becomes a security incident.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-sm-2">
        {% include 'icon-bubble-exclamation' %}
        {% include 'icon-yield-sign' %}
      </div>
      <div class="col-sm-4">
        <h2 class="HeaderB-Level4 mb-4">What Is A Security Alert?</h2>
        <p class="lh-17">A security alert is a notification of a particular event that has occurred. It’s sent to those responsible for investigating further. The SIEM handles the alerts to keep everyone in the loop.</p>
        <h2 class="HeaderB-Level4">What Is A Security Incident?</h2>
        <p class="lh-17">A security incident is an event that resulted in damage that negatively effected the confidentiality, integrity or availability of a business. An incident needs attention immediately to properly resolve or mitgate the impact.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
